{
  "texts": [
    "For reference, a size of 1.0 is ~65 visual degrees, and a position of 0.5 is 90 visual degrees to the right from centre.",
    "• Vary female position: the female varied only her lateral position (with a fixed size of 0.8 and a rotation angle of 0° facing away from the male) from left to right (75 frames) then right to left (75 frames).",
    "Positions were linearly sampled in equal intervals between the range of -0.1 and 0.5.",
    "This range of positions was biased to the right side of the visual field to account for the fact that the projection screen was oriented in the male's right visual hemifield.",
    "After the initial pass of left to right and right to left (150 frames total), we repeated this same pass two more times with shorter periods (100 frames and 50 frames in total, respectively), interpolating positions in the same manner as the initial pass."
  ]
}